(2) Stay by Court which passed the decree.--Where an application is made for stay of execution of an appealable decree before the expiration of the time allowed for appealing therefrom, the Court which passed the decree may on sufficient cause being shown order the execution to be stayed.
(3) No order for stay of execution shall be made under subrule (1) or subrule (2) unless the Court making it is satisfied-- (a) that substantial loss may result to the party applying for stay of execution unless the order is made;
C/SCA/9590/2023 JUDGMENT DATED: 01/07/2023 (b) that the application has been made without unreasonable delay; and (c) that security has been given by the applicant for the due performance of such decree or order as may ultimately be binding upon him.
